@Chris,
I’m not a gamer, so RPG didn’t come naturally, but I had _EDWINE, so I figure it had to be REDWINE….  Then on the right hand side, I had SUPERN___, so filling in OVA was easy even for me, even though I don’t recall knowing that title. 

But I get your HiP/HEP dilemma, as well as the Mexican State. Trivet was a word I learned after I was dating my (now) wife, so I’ve been kind of surprised to learn today that quite a few didn’t know it - something else to thank my wife for when she gets home tonight. And TEASE was easy after I had NOVA, and also helped me with the spelling of HEINIE (avoiding any temptation for the -ey ending instead of -ie).

